# Selected Use Cases

This document presents several key use cases that demonstrate the core functionality of the **My Daniel** information system.

The selected use cases represent the main operational processes identified during the organizational analysis phase and illustrate how the system addresses the organization's business needs.

---

# UC-01 — Activity Resource Assignment

## Goal

Assign the required resources to a planned activity, including instructors and boats.

## Primary Actor

- Coordinator

## Supporting Actors

- Instructor
- Boat

## Description

The system allows the coordinator to assign the required resources to a scheduled activity, including instructors and boats, ensuring that every activity has the resources necessary for safe and effective execution.

## Business Value

- Improves activity planning
- Prevents resource conflicts
- Ensures operational readiness

---

# UC-02 — Activity Resource Modification

## Goal

Modify resources assigned to an existing activity.

## Primary Actor

- Coordinator

## Supporting Actors

- Instructor
- Boat

## Description

The system allows the coordinator to update resources assigned to an existing activity, including replacing instructors, changing boats, or updating equipment assignments in response to operational changes or unexpected situations.

## Business Value

- Supports operational flexibility
- Enables real-time adjustments
- Reduces scheduling disruptions

---

# UC-03 — Participant Attendance Reporting

## Goal

Record participant attendance for an activity.

## Primary Actor

- Instructor

## Supporting Actors

- Customer

## Description

The system allows instructors to report participant attendance by indicating whether a participant attended, was absent with prior notice, or was absent without notice. Instructors may also document exceptional events that occurred during the activity.

## Business Value

- Maintains accurate attendance records
- Improves participant monitoring
- Supports operational reporting

---

# UC-04 — Payroll and Activity Synchronization

## Goal

Validate employee attendance reports against actual activities.

## Primary Actor

- Employee

## Supporting Actors

- Accounting Manager
- Coordinator

## Description

The system automatically synchronizes employee attendance reports with actual recorded activity hours and highlights discrepancies for review.

The objective is to reduce payroll reporting errors, minimize manual verification efforts, and improve payroll accuracy.

## Business Value

- Reduces payroll errors
- Improves reporting reliability
- Decreases administrative workload

---

# UC-05 — Digital Registration Form

## Goal

Register a new customer through a digital process.

## Primary Actor

- Customer

## Supporting Actors

- Administrative Employee

## Description

The system allows customers to complete a digital registration form containing personal details, contact information, and required supporting documents.

The process centralizes customer information and reduces manual data entry.

## Business Value

- Accelerates registration
- Reduces data-entry errors
- Improves customer experience

---

# UC-06 — Lesson Cancellation

## Goal

Cancel a scheduled lesson and notify participants.

## Primary Actor

- Coordinator

## Supporting Actors

- Customer

## Description

The system allows coordinators to cancel a scheduled lesson and notify all relevant participants.

The cancellation is documented within the system to ensure proper tracking and communication.

## Business Value

- Improves communication
- Maintains activity history
- Supports operational management

---

# Summary

The selected use cases represent the most significant operational capabilities of the My Daniel system. Together, they support activity planning, attendance management, payroll validation, customer registration, communication, and day-to-day operational flexibility.

These use cases directly address the business problems identified during the organizational analysis phase and serve as a foundation for the detailed requirements and system design.
